# ============================================================
# calendar.txt   -   one event per line: YYYY-MM-DD  description
# Tags (@health @car @family @subscription @trial ...) are OPTIONAL,
# add one only when an entry feels worth flagging or filtering later.
#
# Tag style: calendar.txt uses @tag (todo.txt style). LIFE.TXT uses
# :tag: (Org-mode style). The difference is intentional - each file
# follows its own lineage, and :tag: colons delimit tags within the
# free-form prose of LIFE.TXT, where @ alone could be ambiguous.
#
# View:  agenda     (today highlighted + upcoming; see: agenda --help)
# Edit:  vi <path>/calendar.txt   - type a dated line anywhere, save.
#
# NOTE: This is a template. The example dates below are illustrative -
# replace them with your own. (Being in the past, they will not show as
# upcoming in agenda until you edit them.)
#
# NOTE: The location is adjustable. agenda reads it from $LIFE_DIR
# (default ~/life, so ~/life/calendar.txt). Set LIFE_DIR to point
# elsewhere, e.g. /mnt/usbflashdrive/life/calendar.txt on a machine
# where life/ lives on a USB drive.
# ============================================================

# ---- STABLE / PRE-POPULATED (rarely changes - birthdays, recurring bills) ----
# Annual birthdays (repeat the date each year, or re-date after it passes):
2026-03-12  @family  Jane Doe's birthday
2026-09-05  @family  John Vega's birthday

# Bills / known due dates:
2026-07-15  @bill  Mortgage payment due (15th monthly)

# Subscriptions started 2026-06-12 (monthly bill on the 12th; re-date as they pass):
2026-07-12  @subscription  TSN - monthly. Still want it?
2026-07-12  @subscription  Netflix - monthly. Still want it?

# A weekly subscription - seed a few, re-seed as they pass:
2026-06-26  @subscription  ExampleWeekly - weekly
2026-07-03  @subscription  ExampleWeekly - weekly

# ---- UPCOMING / SPONTANEOUS (add freely as life happens) ----
2026-06-30  @trial  Example Service trial ends 2026-07-01 - cancel or keep? (started 06-24)
2026-07-02  @health  Dr. - annual checkup 9:30am
